### RegMasks {#a77f67ffaaf31a4a93d170c05933c4e76}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>DenseMap&lt;const Function &#42;, std::vector&lt;uint32&#95;t&gt; &gt; llvm::PhysicalRegisterUsageInfo::RegMasks</>}>
A Dense map from <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a> &#42; to RegMask.

In RegMask 0 means register used (clobbered) by function. and 1 means content of register will be preserved around function call.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/registerusageinfo-h/#l00061">61</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/registerusageinfo-h">RegisterUsageInfo.h</a>.
